-- India cbank says 70 years upper age for pvt bank CEOs, whole-time directors
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury and Neha Dasgupta
-- Tue Sep 09, 2014 05:34AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Sept 9 (Reuters) - The Reserve Bank of India said the upper age limit for managing directors, chief executive officers and other whole-time directors in private banks is 70 years, in line with the Companies Act, 2013.

